name: domcleal-augeasproviders
author: domcleal
description: This module provides alternative providers for core Puppet types using the Augeas configuration API library.

types.name: sshd_config
types.doc:
Manages settings in an OpenSSH sshd_config file.

    The resource name is used for the setting name, but if the `condition` is
    given, then the name can be something else and the `key` given as the name
    of the setting.
  
    Subsystem entries are not managed by this type. There is a specific `sshd_config_subsystem` type to manage these entries.

properties.name: ensure
properties.doc: The basic property that the resource should be in.  Valid values are `present`, `absent`.

properties.name: value

parameters.name: name
parameters.doc: The name of the setting, or a unique string if `condition` given.

parameters.name: key
parameters.doc:
Overrides setting name to prevent resource conflicts if `condition` is
      given.

parameters.name: target
parameters.doc:
The file in which to store the settings, defaults to
      `/etc/ssh/sshd_config`.

parameters.name: condition
parameters.doc:
Match group condition for the entry,
      in the format:

          sshd_config { 'PermitRootLogin':
            value     => 'without-password',
            condition => 'Host example.net',
          }

      The value can contain multiple conditions, concatenated together with
      whitespace.  This is used if the `Match` block has multiple criteria.

          condition => 'Host example.net User root'

providers.name: augeas
providers.doc: Uses Augeas API to update an sshd_config parameter

properties.name: ensure
properties.doc: The basic property that the resource should be in.  Valid values are `present`, `absent`.

properties.name: value
properties.doc: Value to change the setting to. Settings with multiple values (such as net.ipv4.tcp_mem are represented as a single whitespace separated string.

properties.name: comment
properties.doc: Text to be stored in a comment immediately above the entry.  It will be automatically prepended with the name of the setting in order for the provider to know whether it controls the comment or not.

parameters.name: name
parameters.doc: The name of the setting, e.g. net.ipv4.ip_forward

parameters.name: target
parameters.doc:
The file in which to store the settings, defaults to
      `/etc/sysctl.conf`.

providers.name: augeas
providers.doc: Uses Augeas API to update sysctl settings

types.name: sshd_config_subsystem
types.doc: Manages Subsystem settings in an OpenSSH sshd_config file.

properties.name: ensure
properties.doc: The basic property that the resource should be in.  Valid values are `present`, `absent`.

properties.name: command
properties.doc: The command to execute upon subsystem request.

parameters.name: name
parameters.doc: The name of the subsystem to set.

parameters.name: target
parameters.doc:
The file in which to store the settings, defaults to
      `/etc/ssh/sshd_config`.

providers.name: augeas
providers.doc: Uses Augeas API to update a Subsystem parameter in sshd_config.

properties.name: ensure
properties.doc: The basic property that the resource should be in.  Valid values are `present`, `absent`.

properties.name: command
properties.doc: Check command to run on the system, with arguments

parameters.name: name
parameters.doc: The name of the command, e.g. check_my_stuff

parameters.name: target
parameters.doc:
The file in which to store the command, defaults to
      `/etc/nagios/nrpe.cfg`.

providers.name: augeas
providers.doc: Uses Augeas API to update nrpe commands

properties.name: ensure
properties.doc: The basic property that the resource should be in.  Valid values are `present`, `absent`.

properties.name: no_sync
properties.doc: Whether to omit syncing the file after every logging, ony when action_type is file.  Valid values are `true`, `false`.

parameters.name: facility
parameters.doc: The syslog facility for the selector.

parameters.name: level
parameters.doc: The syslog level for the selector.

parameters.name: action_type
parameters.doc: The type of action: file, hostname, user or program.

parameters.name: target
parameters.doc:
The file in which to store the settings, defaults to
      `/etc/syslog.conf`.

parameters.name: lens
parameters.doc: The augeas lens used to parse the file

providers.name: augeas
providers.doc: Uses Augeas API to update a syslog.conf entry
